[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simple, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 8.2. It shows one way you could translate those concepts into working Python code using boto3 and Amazon Comprehend. It is not production-ready. There's no retry logic, no proper error handling, no VPC configuration, and no batch optimization. Think of it as the sketchpad version: useful for understanding how the pieces fit together, not something you'd point at 50,000 real patient surveys. Consider it a starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python installed:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehend:DetectSentiment`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehend:DetectEntities`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehend:ClassifyDocument`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehendmedical:DetectPHI`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:PutObject`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:Query`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `events:PutEvents`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You also need a trained custom classifier endpoint for aspect detection. Training that classifier is covered in the "Gap to Production" section below. For this example, we simulate aspect classification with a rule-based fallback so you can run the pipeline end-to-end without deploying a custom model first.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Configuration and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m These live at the top of the module. The aspect taxonomy and confidence thresholds are configuration, not logic. Edit these as your patient experience team refines what they want to track.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. In production, emit JSON for CloudWatch Logs Insights.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Never log raw patient feedback text (it contains PHI).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Adaptive retry handles Comprehend throttling gracefully.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Module-level clients for reuse in warm Lambda containers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m comprehend_client = boto3.client("comprehend", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m comprehend_medical_client = boto3.client("comprehendmedical", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m events_client = boto3.client("events", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # DynamoDB table for storing analysis results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RESULTS_TABLE_NAME = "sentiment-results"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Confidence threshold for accepting aspect classification predictions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Below this, the aspect assignment is too uncertain to be useful in dashboards.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # 0.6 is conservative; tune based on your labeled validation set.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ASPECT_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.6
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Confidence threshold for triggering the "needs_attention" alert.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # High-confidence negative sentiment on critical aspects gets routed to humans immediately.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ATTENTION_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.85
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Aspects that trigger immediate attention when negative, regardless of confidence.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Pain management and care coordination problems can indicate safety concerns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m CRITICAL_ASPECTS = ["pain_management", "care_coordination"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # The aspect taxonomy. Each entry maps to a category your patient experience team tracks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This should match whatever labels you used to train your custom classifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ASPECT_TAXONOMY = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "wait_time",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "provider_communication",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "staff_interaction",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "facility_environment",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "billing_insurance",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "care_coordination",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "pain_management",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "discharge_process",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "access_convenience",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "overall_experience",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Keyword-based fallback for aspect detection when no custom classifier is deployed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # In production, replace this with a call to your trained Comprehend custom classifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This exists so you can run the full pipeline during development without the classifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ASPECT_KEYWORDS = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "wait_time": ["wait", "waited", "waiting", "delayed", "late", "on time", "appointment time", "schedule"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "provider_communication": ["doctor", "physician", "provider", "explained", "listened", "thorough", "rushed", "dismissive"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "staff_interaction": ["nurse", "staff", "receptionist", "front desk", "friendly", "rude", "helpful"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "facility_environment": ["clean", "dirty", "cold", "hot", "parking", "waiting room", "comfortable", "noise"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "billing_insurance": ["bill", "billing", "charge", "insurance", "cost", "price", "surprise", "statement", "copay"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "care_coordination": ["referral", "follow-up", "follow up", "coordinated", "lost", "fell through", "between doctors"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "pain_management": ["pain", "hurt", "medication", "relief", "suffering", "comfortable"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "discharge_process": ["discharge", "instructions", "leaving", "sent home", "ready to leave"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "access_convenience": ["hours", "location", "telehealth", "virtual", "available", "weekend", "evening"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "overall_experience": ["overall", "experience", "recommend", "return", "general"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: PHI Detection and Redaction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `detect_and_redact_phi(feedback_text)`. This is the mandatory first step: scan the text for protected health information and replace it with type-labeled placeholders. Patient feedback routinely contains provider names, specific diagnoses, medication names, and dates. The redacted version is what flows to all downstream analysis.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def detect_and_redact_phi(feedback_text: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Scan patient feedback for PHI and produce a redacted version.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Uses Amazon Comprehend Medical's DetectPHI API, which is specifically
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     designed to find protected health information in unstructured text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is different from Comprehend's generic PII detection: the medical
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     variant understands clinical entity types like PROCEDURE, MEDICATION,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and DIAGNOSIS that generic PII detection misses.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The redacted text replaces each PHI entity with a bracketed type label.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Example: "Dr. Smith prescribed Metformin" becomes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m              "[NAME] prescribed [MEDICATION]"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This preserves sentence structure and sentiment-bearing words while
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     removing identifiable information. Sentiment analysis works fine on
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     redacted text because the emotional content lives in words like
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "wonderful", "frustrated", "waited" - not in the names and dates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feedback_text: Raw patient feedback text (may contain PHI).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - redacted_text: PHI replaced with type placeholders
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - phi_detected: bool indicating whether any PHI was found
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - entity_count: number of PHI entities detected
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Comprehend Medical DetectPHI has a 20,000 character limit per call.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Patient survey responses rarely exceed this. Call transcripts might.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # For longer texts, you'd chunk by sentence boundary and reassemble.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical_client.detect_phi(Text=feedback_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = response.get("Entities", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the redacted version by replacing entities back-to-front.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Processing from the end of the string backward ensures that character
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # offsets for earlier entities remain valid as we modify the string.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     redacted_text = feedback_text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Sort by BeginOffset descending so we replace from back to front.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sorted_entities = sorted(entities, key=lambda e: e["BeginOffset"], reverse=True)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for entity in sorted_entities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         begin = entity["BeginOffset"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         end = entity["EndOffset"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         entity_type = entity["Type"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Replace the PHI span with a bracketed type label.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # "[NAME]" instead of "Dr. Smith", "[DATE]" instead of "March 15th"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         redacted_text = redacted_text[:begin] + f"[{entity_type}]" + redacted_text[end:]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "PHI detection complete: %d entities found and redacted",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(entities),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "redacted_text": redacted_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "phi_detected": len(entities) > 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "entity_count": len(entities),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Sentiment Analysis
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `analyze_sentiment(redacted_text)`. This calls Amazon Comprehend's built-in sentiment detection on the redacted text. The key insight: store the full score distribution (positive, negative, neutral, mixed), not just the top label. A comment that's 55% negative and 40% positive tells a very different story than one that's 95% negative.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def analyze_sentiment(redacted_text: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run document-level sentiment analysis on the redacted feedback text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns the overall sentiment label plus the full confidence distribution
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     across all four categories. The distribution matters more than the label
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for aggregate analysis: when you average sentiment scores across hundreds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     of feedback items, the nuance in the distribution surfaces trends that
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     binary labels miss.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Comprehend's DetectSentiment supports texts up to 5,000 bytes (UTF-8).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Average patient survey responses are 200-500 characters, well within limits.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         redacted_text: PHI-redacted feedback text from Step 1.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - sentiment: top label (POSITIVE, NEGATIVE, NEUTRAL, MIXED)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - scores: full distribution across all four categories
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - confidence: the highest score (how decisive the classification is)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_client.detect_sentiment(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Text=redacted_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         LanguageCode="en",  # For multilingual populations, detect language first
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scores = response["SentimentScore"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sentiment": response["Sentiment"],  # "POSITIVE", "NEGATIVE", "NEUTRAL", "MIXED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "scores": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "positive": scores["Positive"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "negative": scores["Negative"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "neutral": scores["Neutral"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "mixed": scores["Mixed"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Confidence = how strongly the model believes its top prediction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Low confidence (< 0.5) usually means the text is genuinely mixed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence": max(scores["Positive"], scores["Negative"], scores["Neutral"], scores["Mixed"]),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Aspect Extraction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `extract_aspects(redacted_text, document_sentiment)`. This is where generic sentiment becomes actionable. We split the text into sentences, classify each sentence's aspect, and capture per-aspect sentiment. In production, you'd use a trained Comprehend custom classifier. This example includes a keyword-based fallback so you can run the pipeline without deploying a model first.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def split_into_sentences(text: str) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Split text into sentences using simple heuristics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     A proper NLP sentence tokenizer (like spaCy's) handles edge cases better:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     abbreviations ("Dr."), decimal numbers ("3.5mg"), ellipses ("...").
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This naive split works for typical patient feedback but will occasionally
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     split mid-sentence on abbreviations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For production, use spaCy or NLTK's Punkt tokenizer. We keep this simple
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     here to avoid additional dependencies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Split on period, exclamation, or question mark followed by a space or end of string.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     import re
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sentences = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\s+', text.strip())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Filter out empty strings and very short fragments (< 10 chars).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return [s.strip() for s in sentences if len(s.strip()) >= 10]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_aspect_keyword_fallback(sentence: str) -> tuple:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Fallback aspect classifier using keyword matching.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is NOT what you'd use in production. A trained custom classifier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     understands context: "the doctor kept me waiting" is about wait_time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     not provider_communication, even though "doctor" is present. Keywords
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     can't make that distinction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This exists so you can run the full pipeline end-to-end during development
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     before you've trained and deployed your Comprehend custom classifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Tuple of (aspect_name, confidence_score).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Confidence is synthetic (0.7 for keyword match, 0.3 for no match).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sentence_lower = sentence.lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     best_aspect = "overall_experience"  # default if no keywords match
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     best_score = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for aspect, keywords in ASPECT_KEYWORDS.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         matches = sum(1 for kw in keywords if kw in sentence_lower)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if matches > best_score:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best_score = matches
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best_aspect = aspect
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Synthetic confidence: keyword matching is inherently less reliable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     confidence = 0.7 if best_score > 0 else 0.3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return best_aspect, confidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_aspect_with_comprehend(sentence: str, endpoint_arn: str) -> tuple:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Classify which aspect a sentence discusses using a trained custom classifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the production approach. You train a Comprehend custom classifier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     on labeled healthcare feedback (a few hundred examples per aspect category),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     deploy it to a real-time endpoint, and call ClassifyDocument here.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The endpoint_arn points to your deployed classifier. Training and deployment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     are covered in the Gap to Production section.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sentence: One sentence from the feedback text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         endpoint_arn: ARN of the deployed custom classifier endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Tuple of (aspect_name, confidence_score).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_client.classify_document(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Text=sentence,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         EndpointArn=endpoint_arn,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # ClassifyDocument returns classes sorted by confidence descending.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     top_class = response["Classes"][0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return top_class["Name"], top_class["Score"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def extract_aspects(redacted_text: str, classifier_endpoint_arn: str = None) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Extract aspect-level sentiment from the redacted feedback text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Splits text into sentences, classifies each sentence's aspect, then runs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sentence-level sentiment analysis on each. The output is a list of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (aspect, sentiment, confidence, text) tuples that power the dashboards.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         redacted_text: PHI-redacted feedback text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classifier_endpoint_arn: Optional ARN of trained custom classifier.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             If None, falls back to keyword-based classification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of dicts, each containing:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - aspect: which aspect this sentence discusses
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - sentiment: sentiment toward that aspect
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - sentiment_scores: full distribution for that sentence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - confidence: how confident the aspect classification is
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         - text: the source sentence (for drill-down in dashboards)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sentences = split_into_sentences(redacted_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     aspect_results = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for sentence in sentences:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Classify which aspect this sentence is about.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if classifier_endpoint_arn:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             aspect, aspect_confidence = classify_aspect_with_comprehend(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sentence, classifier_endpoint_arn
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Development fallback: keyword-based classification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             aspect, aspect_confidence = classify_aspect_keyword_fallback(sentence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Only accept aspect classifications above the confidence threshold.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Low-confidence assignments add noise to aggregate dashboards.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if aspect_confidence < ASPECT_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Get sentence-level sentiment for this specific aspect mention.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # This is a separate Comprehend call per sentence. At scale, this is
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # the most expensive part of the pipeline. Batch APIs can help (see
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Gap to Production).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sentence_sentiment = comprehend_client.detect_sentiment(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Text=sentence,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             LanguageCode="en",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         scores = sentence_sentiment["SentimentScore"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         aspect_results.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "aspect": aspect,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sentiment": sentence_sentiment["Sentiment"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sentiment_scores": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "positive": scores["Positive"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "negative": scores["Negative"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "neutral": scores["Neutral"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "mixed": scores["Mixed"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "confidence": aspect_confidence,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "text": sentence,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Extracted %d aspect-sentiment pairs from %d sentences", len(aspect_results), len(sentences))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return aspect_results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Result Assembly and Storage
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `store_analysis_result(source_metadata, sentiment, aspects)`. Combines all outputs into a single DynamoDB record and decides whether this feedback needs immediate human attention. The `needs_attention` flag routes urgent items to the patient experience team in near-real-time rather than waiting for monthly reports.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def determine_needs_attention(document_sentiment: dict, aspects: list) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Decide whether this feedback item needs immediate human review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Criteria:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Overall sentiment is NEGATIVE with high confidence (>= 0.85)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. OR any critical aspect (pain_management, care_coordination) has
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m        negative sentiment, regardless of confidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The second criterion catches safety-related concerns even when the overall
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     document sentiment is mixed. A patient who says "everyone was nice but my
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     pain was never addressed" might score MIXED overall, but the pain_management
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     aspect being negative is an actionable signal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check overall sentiment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         document_sentiment["sentiment"] == "NEGATIVE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         and document_sentiment["confidence"] >= ATTENTION_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check critical aspects.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for aspect_result in aspects:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             aspect_result["aspect"] in CRITICAL_ASPECTS
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             and aspect_result["sentiment"] == "NEGATIVE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_analysis_result(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     source_metadata: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     phi_result: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sentiment: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     aspects: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Assemble the complete analysis record and write it to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The record links back to the source feedback item and includes the full
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     analysis: document-level sentiment, aspect-level sentiments, and processing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     metadata. DynamoDB table design supports queries by date range, department,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     facility, and sentiment for dashboard access patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source_metadata: Dict with feedback_id, channel, department, facility,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                          submitted_date.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         phi_result: Output from detect_and_redact_phi (phi_detected, entity_count).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sentiment: Output from analyze_sentiment (sentiment, scores, confidence).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         aspects: Output from extract_aspects (list of aspect-sentiment pairs).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The full record that was written to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     needs_attention = determine_needs_attention(sentiment, aspects)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Assemble the record. DynamoDB requires Decimal for numeric values.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "feedback_id": source_metadata["feedback_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "source_channel": source_metadata.get("channel", "unknown"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "department": source_metadata.get("department", "unknown"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "facility": source_metadata.get("facility", "unknown"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "analysis_date": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "feedback_date": source_metadata.get("submitted_date", ""),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "document_sentiment": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sentiment": sentiment["sentiment"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "scores": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 k: Decimal(str(round(v, 4)))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 for k, v in sentiment["scores"].items()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "confidence": Decimal(str(round(sentiment["confidence"], 4))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "aspects": [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "aspect": a["aspect"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "sentiment": a["sentiment"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": Decimal(str(round(a["confidence"], 4))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "text": a["text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for a in aspects
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "phi_detected": phi_result["phi_detected"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "needs_attention": needs_attention,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Write to DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results_table = dynamodb.Table(RESULTS_TABLE_NAME)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results_table.put_item(Item=record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # If this needs attention, emit an EventBridge event for alerting.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if needs_attention:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Find the most negative aspect to include in the alert detail.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         negative_aspects = [a for a in aspects if a["sentiment"] == "NEGATIVE"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         top_negative = negative_aspects[0]["aspect"] if negative_aspects else "overall"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         events_client.put_events(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             Entries=[
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "Source": "patient-sentiment-pipeline",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "DetailType": "NegativeSentimentAlert",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "Detail": json.dumps({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "feedback_id": source_metadata["feedback_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "department": source_metadata.get("department"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "facility": source_metadata.get("facility"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "top_negative_aspect": top_negative,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         "confidence": sentiment["confidence"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     }),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Alert emitted for feedback_id=%s (aspect: %s)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source_metadata["feedback_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             top_negative,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into a single function with synthetic test data so you can run it end-to-end.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Synthetic patient feedback for testing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These are fabricated examples that demonstrate different sentiment patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Never use real patient feedback in development environments.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SYNTHETIC_FEEDBACK = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "feedback_id": "survey-2026-03-15-00847",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "channel": "post_visit_survey",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "department": "internal_medicine",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "facility": "main_campus",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "submitted_date": "2026-03-15T14:30:00Z",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "text": (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "The doctor was very thorough and explained everything clearly. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "But I waited 45 minutes past my appointment time and nobody told me why. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "The waiting room was freezing cold. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Then billing sent me a surprise charge three weeks later that nobody mentioned during the visit."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "feedback_id": "survey-2026-03-15-00848",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "channel": "post_visit_survey",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "department": "orthopedics",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "facility": "main_campus",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "submitted_date": "2026-03-15T16:45:00Z",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "text": (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "My knee surgery went perfectly and Dr. Martinez was excellent. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "The nursing staff checked on me regularly and always responded quickly when I called. "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "I would absolutely recommend this practice to anyone needing orthopedic care."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "feedback_id": "survey-2026-03-16-00102",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "channel": "complaint_hotline",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "department": "emergency",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "facility": "west_campus",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "submitted_date": "2026-03-16T08:12:00Z",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "text": (
